definition.value: A province in Kazakhstan.

One of the 26 regions of Tanzania. Kibaha serves as the region's capital. The region is bordered to the North by the Tanga Region, to the East by Dar-es-Salaam and the Indian Ocean, to the South by the Lindi Region and to the West by the Morogoro Region.
One of the regions of Tanzania. The capital of the region is the city of Dodoma.
One of Tanzania's 26 administrative regions. The regional capital is Iringa.
One of Tanzania's 26 administrative regions. The regional capital is Bukoba. The region neighbors Uganda, Rwanda and Burundi and lies across Lake Victoria from Kenya.

One of Tanzania's 26 administrative regions. The regional capital is Kigoma. It is bordered to the North by the Kagera Region, to the East by the Shinyanga and Tabora Regions, to the South by the Rukwa Region, to the West by Lake Tanganyika which forms a border with the Democratic Republic of the Congo and to the Northwest by Burundi.
One of the 26 regions in Tanzania. The capital of the region is Moshi.

One of Tanzania's 26 administrative regions. The regional capital is Lindi. The Lindi region borders on Pwani, Morogoro, Ruvuma, and Mtwara. Much of the western part of the region is in the Selous Game Reserve.

One of the 26 Regions of Tanzania. Babati serves as the Region's capital. It is bordered to the North by the Arusha Region, to the Northeast by the Kilimanjaro Region, to the East by the Tanga Region, to the South by the Dodoma Region, to the Southwest by the Singida Region and to the Northwest by the Shinyanga Region.

One of the 26 regions of Tanzania. The region is named after the Mara River. Musoma serves as the Region's capital. The neighbouring regions are Mwanza and Shinyanga(to the south), Arusha (to the south east)and Kagera (through Lake Victoria). To the north east, it borders the Republic of Kenya.

One of Tanzania's 26 administrative regions. The regional capital is Mbeya. It is bordered to the northwest by Tabora Region, to the northeast by Singida Region, to the East by Iringa Region, to the South by Zambia and Malawi and to the West by Rukwa Region.

One of the regions of Tanzania. The boundary with Mozambique to the south is formed by the Ruvuma River. To the west, the Mtwara Region is bordered by the Ruvuma Region, to the North, by the Lindi Region, and to the East the region is bordered by the Indian Ocean.

One of the regions of Tanzania. Its capital is Mwanza. The neighbouring regions are Kagera to the west, Shinyanga to the south, and Mara to the east. Furthermore, Lake Victoria is neighbouring to the North.
One of the 26 regions of Tanzania. Located on Pemba Island, the region's capital is Wete.
One of the 26 regions of Tanzania. Located on Pemba Island, the region's capital is Mkoani.

One of the 26 regions of Tanzania. Sumbawanga serves as the region's capital. The region is bordered to the north by Kigoma and Tabora Regions, to the East by Mbeya Region, to the South by Zambia and to the West by Lake Tanganyika which forms a border between the region and the Democratic Republic of the Congo.

One of the regions of Tanzania. The Ruvuma River forms most of its southern boundary with Mozambique. It is also bordered to the North by the Morogoro Region, to the Northeast by the Lindi Region, to the East by the Mtwara Region and to the Northwest by the Iringa Region.

One of the regions of Tanzania. Its capital is Shinyanga. It is bordered to the north by the Mwanza, Mara, and Kagera Regions, and to the south by the Tabora Region. Kigoma Region borders to the west, Singida Region to the southeast, and the Arusha and Manyara Regions to the east.

One of the regions of Tanzania. The region is bordered to the North by Shinyanga Region, to the Northeast by Manyara Region, to the East by Dodoma Region, to the Southeast by Iringa Region, to the Southwest by Mbeya Region and to the West by Tabora Region.
One of the regions of Tanzania. Its capital is Tabora town.
One of the 26 regions of Tanzania. Located on the island of Zanzibar, Mkokotoni serves as the region's capital.
One of the 26 regions of Tanzania. Located on the island of Unguja, Zanzibar Town serves as the region's capital.
One of the 26 regions of Tanzania. Located on the island of Zanzibar, Koani serves as the region's capital.
One of the 21 aimags (provinces) of Mongolia. It is located in the south of the country, approximately 245 km south of Ulaanbaatar. Its capital is Mandalgovi.
One of the 21 aimags of Mongolia. It is located in the south of the country. Its capital is Bayankhongor.
One of the 21 aimags (provinces) of Mongolia. The national capital Ulan Bator is located roughly at its center, but the city itself is administrated as an independent municipality.
One of the 21 Aimags (provinces) of Mongolia. It is located in the southeast of the country.
One of the 21 aimags (provinces) of Mongolia. It is located in the center of the country. Its capital is Choir.
One of the 21 aimags (provinces) of Mongolia. It is located in the north of the country. The Darkhan-Uul aimag with its four sum was carved out of the Selenge aimag in 1994.

One of the 21 aimags (provinces) of Mongolia, located in the east of the country. Its capital is Ondorkhaan. The aimag borders with Russia in the north. The neighbouring aimags are Darkhan-Uul in the northwest, Tov in the west, Govisumber in the southwest, Dornogovi in the south, Sukhbaatar in the southeast, and Dornod in the east. The border to Tov is divided by the city of Baganuur, an administrative exclave of Ulan Bator.

One of the 21 aimags (provinces) of Mongolia, located in northern Mongolia. The aimag is surrounded by the aimags Khovsgol in the northwest, Arkhangai in the southwest, Ovorkhangai in the south, Tov in the southeast, and Selenge in the northeast. The small Orkhon Aimag forms an enclave at the border to Selenge.
The easternmost of the 21 aimags (provinces) of Mongolia. Its capital is Choibalsan.

One of the 21 aimags (provinces) of Mongolia. It is located in the west of the country, 1336 km away from the national capital Ulan Bator. Its capital is Ulaangom. In the north the province borders the Russian Federation for 640 km, in the east 340 km of border lies between Uvs and Zavkhan province. In the south and west it borders with Khovd and Bayan-Olgii provinces for 200 km each.
One of the 21 aimags (provinces) of Mongolia, located in the west of the country. Its capital is Uliastai.

The westernmost of the 21 aimags (provinces) of Mongolia. The aimag was established in 1940. The aimag is located in the extreme west of the country, and shares borders with both Russia and China. The border between the two neighbouring countries is very short here, though, and ends after about 40 km at the eastern end of Kazakhstan. Within Mongolia, the neighbouring aimags are Uvs in the north east and Khovd in the south east.
One of the 21 aimags (provinces) of Mongolia. It is located in the west of the country.

One of the 21 Aimags (provinces) of Mongolia. It is located slightly west to the country's center, on the northern slopes of the Khangai Mountains. The Arkhangai aimag is located in the interior of the country and borders to the following other aimags: Bulgan (north east), Ovorkhangai (south east), Bayankhongor (south), Zavkhan (west), and Khovsgol (north west).
One of the 21 aimags (provinces) of Mongolia, located in the north of the country. The capital is Sukhbaatar.
An aimag (province) of Mongolia, located in the south of the country, in the Gobi Desert. The capital is Dalanzadgad.
One of the 21 aimags (provinces) of Mongolia, located in the west of the country. Its capital is also named Khovd.

One of the 21 Aimags (provinces) of Mongolia, located in the north of the country. Its capital is Erdenet. Parts of the Orkhon Valley Cultural Landscape are situated in this province. This Aimag was cut out of Bulgan Aimag in 1994, to form a new entity together with its capital Erdenet, which had previously been administrated as a federal municipality.
The northernmost of the 21 aimags (provinces) of Mongolia.
One of the 21 aimags (provinces) of Mongolia, located in the south of the country. Its capital is Arvaikheer.
One of the 21 aimags of Mongolia, located in the east of the country. Its capital is Baruun-Urt.
A province of Mozambique. Xai-Xai is the capital of the province. Located to the east is the Inhambane Province, to the north is Manica Province, and to the south is Maputo Province.
The northernmost province of Mozambique.

A province of Mozambique located on the coast in the southern part of the country. Inhambane faz fronteira a norte com as provincias de Sofala e Manica, a leste e sudeste com o Oceano Indico e a sul e oeste com a provincia de Gaza.

A province of Mozambique. Faz fronteira com as provincias de Cabo Delgado e Niassa, a Norte, das quais esta separada pelo rio Lurio; com a Zambezia a sudoeste (separada pelo rio Ligonha) e com o Oceano Indico a este.
A province of Mozambique, located in the central coastal region south of Nampula and north of Sofala. The provincial capital is Quelimane on the Bons Sinais River.
